narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Intensive, but extremely rewarding, second year in Chinese. If you've taken L1/L2, I don't see why you wouldn't want to take this.
It is a good place to start if you have already taken some Chinese during high school... Not too much workload but not too easy.
If you want to really learn Chinese regardless of workload, it's a good course. If you have tight schedule elsewhere, don't.
